Fascinating observation. Maybe the real question should be, how many of us can say we haven't at least toyed with the idea of launching a "next Skype" ourselves? It's easy to get complacent with what's worked before. 

Just think about how many "next big thing" startups are trying to reinvent the wheel instead of building on the wheel that's already proven its longevity.

Ironically, perhaps Skype's downfall was a missed opportunity to leverage its user base and evolve,